text: The Prime Minister of Kuwait is the head of government of Kuwait. As the third most powerful official in the country, following the Emir of Kuwait and Speaker of the National Assembly, the prime minister leads the executive branch of the Government of Kuwait. ==List== List of the Prime Ministers of Kuwait: Name Reigned from Reigned until 1 Sabah I bin Jaber (Sabah I) 1752 1762 2 Abdullah I al-Sabah (Abdullah I) 1762 3 May 1814 3 Jaber I al-Sabah (Jaber I) 1814 1859 4 Sabah II al-Sabah (Sabah II) 1859 November 1866 5 Abdullah II al-Sabah (Abdullah II) November 1866 1892 6 Muhammad al-Sabah (Muhammad I) May 1892 1896 7 Mubarak al-Sabah (Mubarak I) 18 May 1896 28 November 1915 8 Jaber II al-Sabah (Jaber II) 28 November 1915 2 February 1917 9 Salim al-Mubarak al-Sabah (Salim I) 5 February 1917 22 February 1921 10 Ahmad al-Jaber al-Sabah (Ahmad I) 29 March 1921 29 January 1950 11 Abdullah al-Salim al-Sabah (Abdullah III) 29 January 1950 26 January 1963 12 Sabah Al- Salim Al-Sabah 2 February 1963 27 November 1965 13 Jaber Al-Ahmad Al-Sabah 27 November 1965 8 February 1978 14 Saad Al-Salim Al-Sabah 8 February 1978 13 July 2003 15 Sabah Al-Ahmad Al-Jaber Al-Sabah 13 July 2003 30 January 2006 16 Nasser Al-Mohammed Al-Sabah 7 February 2006 28 November 2011 17 Jaber Al- Mubarak Al-Hamad Al-Sabah 30 November 2011 19 November 2019 18 Sabah Al-Khalid Al-Sabah 19 November 2019 19 July 2022 19 Ahmad Nawaf Al-Ahmad Al-Sabah (born 1956) 24 July 2022 17 January 2024 20 Mohammad Sabah Al-Salem Al-Sabah 17 January 2024 15 May 2024 21 Ahmad Al-Abdullah Al-Sabah أحمد عبد الله الأحمد الصباح 15 May 2024 Incumbent ==References==
